131.5	Simon_(game)	Simon (game)	Simon is an electronic game of memory skill invented by Ralph H. Baer and Howard J. Morrison, with the software programming being done by Lenny Cope and manufactured and distributed by Milton Bradley. Simon was launched in 1978 at Studio 54 in New York City and was an immediate success, becoming a pop culture symbol of the 1980s.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/OriginalSimon.jpg/200px-OriginalSimon.jpg
